lod/1",{"ana":56},"#text_condition.incomplete #text_condition.legible",{"lettering":58,"dimensions":59},"Relatively tall and thin letters, but still of regular square form, of somewhat irregular width, with short basic serifs at the end of strokes; somewhat roughly chiselled. R has an extended tail which does not reach to the lower line; O is tall and narrow; E has slightly shorter middle stroke. M is narrow, with very short middle strokes that join at the midpoint and join  the verticals well below the top.",[60,68,75],{"type":61,"l":62,"from":63,"to":63,"h":64,"unit":65,"atLeast":66,"atMost":67},"letterHeight","Line 2","line2","70-75","mm","70","75",{"type":69,"l":70,"from":71,"to":63,"h":72,"unit":65,"atLeast":73,"atMost":74},"interlinear","Interlineation line 1 to 2","line1","17-23","17","23",{"type":69,"l":76,"from":63,"to":77,"h":78,"unit":65,"atLeast":79,"atMost":43},"Interlineation line 2 to 3","line3","25-30","25",{"_":81,"notBefore":82,"notAfter":83,"evidence":84},"later imperial (later 2nd — 4th centuries CE?)",151,400,"lettering, material-context",[86,91],{"_":87,"type":88,"ref":89,"region":90},"Syracusae","ancient","http://pleiades.stoa.org/places/462503","Sicilia",{"_":92,"type":93,"ref":94,"region":90},"Siracusa","modern","http://sws.geonames.org/2523083",[96],[97,98],37.08415,15.27628,{"_":100,"type":101,"notAfter":102,"geo":17},"Of uncertain provenance, first noted in the first volume of the museum inventory, compiled in 1885","found","1885",[],{"_":105,"type":106,"geo":17},"Magazzino B, cassetta 16","observed",[108,115],{"n":109,"url":110,"height":111,"width":112,"desc":113,"surfaceType":114},"screen","ISic004360_tiled.tif","3680px","5520px","Photo J. Prag, Aut. Assessorato Beni Culturali Regione Siciliana n.10681 del 06/05/2014","front",{"n":109,"url":116,"height":111,"width":112,"desc":113,"surfaceType":117},"ISic004360_rear_tiled.tif","rear","Sicily",{"_":120,"role":121,"ref":122,"museum":123},"Museo Archeologico Regionale Paolo Orsi","museum","http://sicily.classics.ox.ac.uk/museum/097",{"slug":124,"type":121,"name":120,"uri":122,"description":125,"location":126},"097","An outstanding collection of archaeological material. The collection ranges from Siracusa and the surrounding territory (Megara Hyblaia, Akrai, Kasmenai etc) to encompass all of eastern Sicily, reaching as far as Gela and Agrigento. The ground floor covers prehistory through to the end of the Classical period. Upstairs includes Hellenistic and Roman Syracuse and a display of material from the catacombs. A gallery displaying material from Hellenistic eastern Sicily is in preparation.",{"settlement":92,"region":92,"country":127,"address":128,"geo":129},"Italy","Viale Teocrito 66, 96100 - Siracusa",{"lat":130,"lon":131},37.07636989,15.2866213,{"_":133,"type":134},"255","inventory",{"_":136,"mainLang":137,"languages":138},"Latin","la",[136],{"type":140,"bibl":141},"edition",[142,155],{"type":143,"n":144,"author":145,"title":146,"date":147,"citedRange":148,"ptr":149,"ref":150,"inscriptionDate":151,"citation":152,"uri":153,"year":154},"bulletin","NSA","","Notizie degli scavi di antichità","1876-","386",{"target":150},"https://www.zotero.org/groups/382445/items/4MCP2PVV","1889","\u003Cspan>Accademia nazionale dei Lincei, Istituto nazionale di archeologia e storia dell’arte (Italy), e Reale Accademia d’Italia, «Notizie degli scavi di antichità», \u003Ci>Notizie degli Scavi di Antichità\u003C/i>, 1876, \u003Ca href=\"http://www.worldcat.org/oclc/1646037\">http://www.worldcat.org/oclc/1646037\u003C/a>\u003C/span>","https://www.zotero.org/groups/isicily/items/4MCP2PVV","1876",{"author":156,"date":157,"citedRange":158,"ptr":159,"ref":161,"inscriptionDate":157,"title":163,"citation":164,"uri":165,"year":157},"Orsi","2018","Tacc. 1, p.46",{"target":160},"https://www.zotero.org/groups/382445/items/RGRSRUHK",{"_":162,"target":162},"https://biblio.inscriptiones.org/epig10002617","I Taccuini. I. Riproduzione anastatica e trascrizione dei Taccuini 1-4","\u003Cspan>Paolo Orsi, \u003Ci>I Taccuini. I. Riproduzione anastatica e trascrizione dei Taccuini 1-4\u003C/i>, a c. di Gioconda Lamagna e Giuseppina Monterosso, Accademia Nazionale dei Lincei. Monumenti Antichi. Serie Miscellanea 20 (Rome: Giorgio Bretschneider Editore, 2018)\u003C/span>","https://www.zotero.org/groups/isicily/items/RGRSRUHK",{"type":167,"bibl":168},"discussion",[17],{"editor":170,"principal":173,"contributors":174,"change":194},{"_":171,"ref":172},"Jonathan Prag","#JP",{"_":171,"ref":172},[175,178,182,186,190],{"_":171,"xml:id":176,"ref":177},"JP","http://orcid.org/0000-0003-3819-8537",{"_":179,"xml:id":180,"ref":181},"James Cummings","JCu","http://orcid.org/0000-0002-6686-3728",{"_":183,"xml:id":184,"ref":185},"Simona Stoyanova","SS","https://orcid.org/0000-0003-3914-9569",{"_":187,"xml:id":188,"ref":189},"Valentina Mignosa","VM","https://orcid.org/0000-0002-7122-2511",{"_":191,"xml:id":192,"ref":193},"Alessia Coccato","Coccato","https://orcid.org/0000-0002-6641-2820",{"_":195,"when":196,"who":172},"Jonathan Prag edited from autopsy, revising text, adding image, bibliography, metadata","2021-03-03",{"n":109,"url":110,"height":111,"width":112,"desc":113,"surfaceType":114},[199,202,205],{"atLeast":200,"atMost":201},70,75,{"atLeast":203,"atMost":204},17,23,{"atLeast":206,"atMost":207},25,30,[209,210],"Notizie degli scavi di antichità, 1876-","Orsi, 2018, I Taccuini. I. Riproduzione anastatica e trascrizione dei Taccuini 1-4",[212,213],"4MCP2PVV","RGRSRUHK",[215,216,217,19,24,28,218,219,220,221,219,222,223,137],"isic004360","i.sicily inscription 004360",{"_":5},"syracusae","siracusa","sicilia","sicily","museo archeologico regionale paolo orsi","latin",[],{"title":226,"body":227,"divs":228,"editions":253,"images":263,"handnote":274},"ISic004360. I.Sicily inscription 004360","\u003Cdiv id=\"editions\">\u003Cdiv class=\"attribution\">Text encoding: Jonathan Prag\u003C/div>\u003Cdiv id=\"edition-interpretive\" lang=\"la\">  \u003Cdiv class=\"textpart\" lang=\"la\">\u003Cspan class=\"ab\" id=\"div-interpretive\">  \u003Ca id=\"al1-interpretive\">\u003C!--0-->\u003C/a>\u003Cspan class=\"linenumber\">1\u003C/span>[\u003Cspan dir=\"ltr\" class=\"gap\">---\u003C/span>]ṚỊẠṂ\u003Cspan dir=\"ltr\" class=\"gap\">...\u003C/span>[\u003Cspan dir=\"ltr\" class=\"gap\">---\u003C/span>] \u003Cbr id=\"al2-interpretive\">\u003Cspan class=\"linenumber\">2\u003C/span>[\u003Cspan dir=\"ltr\" class=\"gap\">---\u003C/span> in mel]ịorem faci[em\u003Cspan dir=\"ltr\" class=\"gap\">---\u003C/span>] \u003Cbr id=\"al3-interpretive\">\u003Cspan class=\"linenumber\">3\u003C/span>[\u003Cspan dir=\"ltr\" class=\"gap\">---\u003C/span>]USUIS\u003Cspan dir=\"ltr\" class=\"gap\">.\u003C/span>[\u003Cspan dir=\"ltr\" class=\"gap\">---\u003C/span>] \u003C/span>\u003C/div>  \u003Cp class=\"miniapp\">\u003C/p>\u003C/div>\u003Cdiv class=\"attribution\">Text encoding: Jonathan Prag\u003C/div>\u003Cdiv id=\"edition-diplomatic\" lang=\"la\">\u003Cdiv class=\"textpart\" lang=\"la\">\u003Cspan class=\"ab\" id=\"div-diplomatic\">\u003Ca id=\"al1-diplomatic\">\u003C!--0-->\u003C/a>\u003Cspan class=\"linenumber\">1\u003C/span>[\u003Cspan dir=\"ltr\" class=\"gap\">---\u003C/span>]....\u003Cspan dir=\"ltr\" class=\"gap\">···\u003C/span>[\u003Cspan dir=\"ltr\" class=\"gap\">---\u003C/span>]\u003Cbr id=\"al2-diplomatic\">\u003Cspan class=\"linenumber\">2\u003C/span>[\u003Cspan dir=\"ltr\" class=\"gap\">---\u003C/span>.....].OREMFACI[..\u003Cspan dir=\"ltr\" class=\"gap\">---\u003C/span>]\u003Cbr id=\"al3-diplomatic\">\u003Cspan class=\"linenumber\">3\u003C/span>[\u003Cspan dir=\"ltr\" class=\"gap\">---\u003C/span>]USUIS\u003Cspan dir=\"ltr\" class=\"gap\">·\u003C/span>[\u003Cspan dir=\"ltr\" class=\"gap\">---\u003C/span>]\u003C/span>\u003C/div>\u003Cp class=\"miniapp\">\u003C/p>\u003C/div>\u003C/div>  \u003Cdiv id=\"facsimile-images\">\u003Ch2>Facsimile Images\u003C/h2>\u003Ca href=\"ISic004360_tiled.tif\">\u003Cimg title=\"Photo J. Prag, Aut. Assessorato Beni Culturali Regione Siciliana n.10681 del 06/05/2014\" src=\"ISic004360_tiled-thumb.tif\">\u003C/a>\u003Ca href=\"ISic004360.jpg\">\u003Cimg title=\"Photo J. Prag, Aut. Assessorato Beni Culturali Regione Siciliana n.10681 del 06/05/2014\" src=\"ISic004360-thumb.jpg\">\u003C/a>\u003Ca href=\"ISic004360_rear_tiled.tif\">\u003Cimg title=\"Photo J. Prag, Aut. Assessorato Beni Culturali Regione Siciliana n.10681 del 06/05/2014\" src=\"ISic004360_rear_tiled-thumb.tif\">\u003C/a>\u003Ca href=\"ISic004360_rear.jpg\">\u003Cimg title=\"Photo J. Prag, Aut. Assessorato Beni Culturali Regione Siciliana n.10681 del 06/05/2014\" src=\"ISic004360_rear-thumb.jpg\">\u003C/a>\u003C/div>  \u003Cdiv id=\"apparatus\">\u003Ch4>Apparatus criticus\u003C/h4>\u003Cul>\u003Cli>\u003Cspan class=\"line 1\">line.1: \u003Cspan>Orsi (NSA): Riam. . . .; Orsi (Taccuini): RIAMIR . The first three characters are almost certainly RIA, followed by four verticals grouped in two pairs, either or both of which would be compatible with M as in line 2, followed by two further marks slightly above the line; Orsi's suggestion is entirely plausible.\u003C/span>\u003C/span>\u003Cbr>\u003C/li>\u003Cli>\u003Cspan class=\"line 2\">line.2: \u003Cspan>Orsi: IOREMFACI; the top of a vertical is visible at the start of the line\u003C/span>\u003C/span>\u003Cbr>\u003C/li>\u003Cli>\u003Cspan class=\"line 3\">line.3: \u003Cspan>The trace of a downward right slanting stroke is visible at the upper right end of the line, compatible with V, X or Y (also noted by Orsi, Taccuini)\u003C/span>\u003C/span>\u003C/li>\u003C/ul>\u003C/div>  \u003Cdiv id=\"translation\">\u003Ch2> translation\u003C/h2>\u003Cp class=\"translation-author\">  \u003C/p>\u003Cp>  \u003C/p>\u003C/div>  \u003Cdiv id=\"commentary\">\u003Ch2>commentary\u003C/h2>  \u003Cp>This text is on the reverse of what was originally a large monumental Latin inscription of the first or second century AD (see \u003Ca href=\"http://sicily.classics.ox.ac.uk/inscription/ISic001671\" target=\"_blank\">ISic001671\u003C/a>), and so this text is presumably secondary re-use of the stone and the later text from its form. Line 2 can reasonably be restored to suggest that this was a text recording the rebuilding or reconstruction of a structure of some sort. On that basis, the word in line 1 is perhaps most likely to be 'memoria' or 'gloria', and line 3 may contain reference to the individual responsible. The text does not appear to have been republished or discussed since Orsi. Orsi recorded it in the first of his taccuini, prior to publishing it in the NSA. Curiously, in neither case did he note the presence of a text on the reverse, which fact is recorded in the inventory (it is possible that the text was already fixed to the wall for display when he saw it?).\u003C/p>  \u003C/div>  \u003Cdiv id=\"bibliography\">\u003Ch2>bibliography\u003C/h2>  \u003Cul>\u003Cli> Orsi NSA 1889 386 \u003Ca href=\"https://biblio.inscriptiones.org/epig10001392\" target=\"_blank\">https://biblio.inscriptiones.org/epig10001392\u003C/a>\u003C/li>\u003Cli> Orsi 2018 Tacc. 1, p.46 \u003Ca href=\"https://biblio.inscriptiones.org/epig10002617\" target=\"_blank\">https://biblio.inscriptiones.org/epig10002617\u003C/a>\u003C/li>\u003C/ul>  \u003Cul>\u003Cli>\u003C/li>\u003C/ul>  \u003C/div>  \u003Cdiv id=\"handnote\">\u003Cp>Relatively tall and thin letters, but still of regular square form, of somewhat irregular width, with short basic serifs at the end of strokes; somewhat roughly chiselled. R has an extended tail which does not reach to the lower line; O is tall and narrow; E has slightly shorter middle stroke. M is narrow, with very short middle strokes that join at the midpoint and join the verticals well below the top.\u003C/p> Line 2  70-75  Interlineation line 1 to 2  17-23  Interlineation line 2 to 3  25-30  \u003C/div>\u003Cdiv id=\"license\"> Licensed under a Creative Commons-Attribution 4.0 licence \u003C/div>",[229,232,235,238,241,244,247,250],{"id":230,"html":231},"editions","\u003Cdiv class=\"attribution\">Text encoding: Jonathan Prag\u003C/div>\u003Cdiv id=\"edition-interpretive\" lang=\"la\">  \u003Cdiv class=\"textpart\" lang=\"la\">\u003Cspan class=\"ab\" id=\"div-interpretive\">  \u003Ca id=\"al1-interpretive\">\u003C!--0-->\u003C/a>\u003Cspan class=\"linenumber\">1\u003C/span>[\u003Cspan dir=\"ltr\" class=\"gap\">---\u003C/span>]ṚỊẠṂ\u003Cspan dir=\"ltr\" class=\"gap\">...\u003C/span>[\u003Cspan dir=\"ltr\" class=\"gap\">---\u003C/span>] \u003Cbr id=\"al2-interpretive\">\u003Cspan class=\"linenumber\">2\u003C/span>[\u003Cspan dir=\"ltr\" class=\"gap\">---\u003C/span> in mel]ịorem faci[em\u003Cspan dir=\"ltr\" class=\"gap\">---\u003C/span>] \u003Cbr id=\"al3-interpretive\">\u003Cspan class=\"linenumber\">3\u003C/span>[\u003Cspan dir=\"ltr\" class=\"gap\">---\u003C/span>]USUIS\u003Cspan dir=\"ltr\" class=\"gap\">.\u003C/span>[\u003Cspan dir=\"ltr\" class=\"gap\">---\u003C/span>] \u003C/span>\u003C/div>  \u003Cp class=\"miniapp\">\u003C/p>\u003C/div>\u003Cdiv class=\"attribution\">Text encoding: Jonathan Prag\u003C/div>\u003Cdiv id=\"edition-diplomatic\" lang=\"la\">\u003Cdiv class=\"textpart\" lang=\"la\">\u003Cspan class=\"ab\" id=\"div-diplomatic\">\u003Ca id=\"al1-diplomatic\">\u003C!--0-->\u003C/a>\u003Cspan class=\"linenumber\">1\u003C/span>[\u003Cspan dir=\"ltr\" class=\"gap\">---\u003C/span>]....\u003Cspan dir=\"ltr\" class=\"gap\">···\u003C/span>[\u003Cspan dir=\"ltr\" class=\"gap\">---\u003C/span>]\u003Cbr id=\"al2-diplomatic\">\u003Cspan class=\"linenumber\">2\u003C/span>[\u003Cspan dir=\"ltr\" class=\"gap\">---\u003C/span>.....].OREMFACI[..\u003Cspan dir=\"ltr\" class=\"gap\">---\u003C/span>]\u003Cbr id=\"al3-diplomatic\">\u003Cspan class=\"linenumber\">3\u003C/span>[\u003Cspan dir=\"ltr\" class=\"gap\">---\u003C/span>]USUIS\u003Cspan dir=\"ltr\" class=\"gap\">·\u003C/span>[\u003Cspan dir=\"ltr\" class=\"gap\">---\u003C/span>]\u003C/span>\u003C/div>\u003Cp class=\"miniapp\">\u003C/p>\u003C/div>",{"id":233,"html":234},"facsimile-images","\u003Ch2>Facsimile Images\u003C/h2>\u003Ca href=\"ISic004360_tiled.tif\">\u003Cimg title=\"Photo J. Prag, Aut. Assessorato Beni Culturali Regione Siciliana n.10681 del 06/05/2014\" src=\"ISic004360_tiled-thumb.tif\">\u003C/a>\u003Ca href=\"ISic004360.jpg\">\u003Cimg title=\"Photo J. Prag, Aut. Assessorato Beni Culturali Regione Siciliana n.10681 del 06/05/2014\" src=\"ISic004360-thumb.jpg\">\u003C/a>\u003Ca href=\"ISic004360_rear_tiled.tif\">\u003Cimg title=\"Photo J. Prag, Aut. Assessorato Beni Culturali Regione Siciliana n.10681 del 06/05/2014\" src=\"ISic004360_rear_tiled-thumb.tif\">\u003C/a>\u003Ca href=\"ISic004360_rear.jpg\">\u003Cimg title=\"Photo J. Prag, Aut. Assessorato Beni Culturali Regione Siciliana n.10681 del 06/05/2014\" src=\"ISic004360_rear-thumb.jpg\">\u003C/a>",{"id":236,"html":237},"apparatus","\u003Ch4>Apparatus criticus\u003C/h4>\u003Cul>\u003Cli>\u003Cspan class=\"line 1\">line.1: \u003Cspan>Orsi (NSA): Riam. . . .; Orsi (Taccuini): RIAMIR . The first three characters are almost certainly RIA, followed by four verticals grouped in two pairs, either or both of which would be compatible with M as in line 2, followed by two further marks slightly above the line; Orsi's suggestion is entirely plausible.\u003C/span>\u003C/span>\u003Cbr>\u003C/li>\u003Cli>\u003Cspan class=\"line 2\">line.2: \u003Cspan>Orsi: IOREMFACI; the top of a vertical is visible at the start of the line\u003C/span>\u003C/span>\u003Cbr>\u003C/li>\u003Cli>\u003Cspan class=\"line 3\">line.3: \u003Cspan>The trace of a downward right slanting stroke is visible at the upper right end of the line, compatible with V, X or Y (also noted by Orsi, Taccuini)\u003C/span>\u003C/span>\u003C/li>\u003C/ul>",{"id":239,"html":240},"translation","\u003Ch2> translation\u003C/h2>\u003Cp class=\"translation-author\">  \u003C/p>\u003Cp>  \u003C/p>",{"id":242,"html":243},"commentary","\u003Ch2>commentary\u003C/h2>  \u003Cp>This text is on the reverse of what was originally a large monumental Latin inscription of the first or second century AD (see \u003Ca href=\"http://sicily.classics.ox.ac.uk/inscription/ISic001671\" target=\"_blank\">ISic001671\u003C/a>), and so this text is presumably secondary re-use of the stone and the later text from its form. Line 2 can reasonably be restored to suggest that this was a text recording the rebuilding or reconstruction of a structure of some sort. On that basis, the word in line 1 is perhaps most likely to be 'memoria' or 'gloria', and line 3 may contain reference to the individual responsible. The text does not appear to have been republished or discussed since Orsi. Orsi recorded it in the first of his taccuini, prior to publishing it in the NSA. Curiously, in neither case did he note the presence of a text on the reverse, which fact is recorded in the inventory (it is possible that the text was already fixed to the wall for display when he saw it?).\u003C/p>  ",{"id":245,"html":246},"bibliography","\u003Ch2>bibliography\u003C/h2>  \u003Cul>\u003Cli> Orsi NSA 1889 386 \u003Ca href=\"https://biblio.inscriptiones.org/epig10001392\" target=\"_blank\">https://biblio.inscriptiones.org/epig10001392\u003C/a>\u003C/li>\u003Cli> Orsi 2018 Tacc. 1, p.46 \u003Ca href=\"https://biblio.inscriptiones.org/epig10002617\" target=\"_blank\">https://biblio.inscriptiones.org/epig10002617\u003C/a>\u003C/li>\u003C/ul>  \u003Cul>\u003Cli>\u003C/li>\u003C/ul>  ",{"id":248,"html":249},"handnote","\u003Cp>Relatively tall and thin letters, but still of regular square form, of somewhat irregular width, with short basic serifs at the end of strokes; somewhat roughly chiselled. R has an extended tail which does not reach to the lower line; O is tall and narrow; E has slightly shorter middle stroke. M is narrow, with very short middle strokes that join at the midpoint and join the verticals well below the top.\u003C/p> Line 2  70-75  Interlineation line 1 to 2  17-23  Interlineation line 2 to 3  25-30  ",{"id":251,"html":252},"license"," Licensed under a Creative Commons-Attribution 4.0 licence ",[254,256,259,260],{"html":255},"Text encoding: Jonathan Prag",{"id":257,"lang":137,"html":258},"edition-interpretive","\u003Cdiv class=\"textpart\" lang=\"la\">\u003Cspan class=\"ab\" id=\"div-interpretive\">  \u003Ca id=\"al1-interpretive\">\u003C!--0-->\u003C/a>\u003Cspan class=\"linenumber\">1\u003C/span>[\u003Cspan dir=\"ltr\" class=\"gap\">---\u003C/span>]ṚỊẠṂ\u003Cspan dir=\"ltr\" class=\"gap\">...\u003C/span>[\u003Cspan dir=\"ltr\" class=\"gap\">---\u003C/span>] \u003Cbr id=\"al2-interpretive\">\u003Cspan class=\"linenumber\">2\u003C/span>[\u003Cspan dir=\"ltr\" class=\"gap\">---\u003C/span> in mel]ịorem faci[em\u003Cspan dir=\"ltr\" class=\"gap\">---\u003C/span>] \u003Cbr id=\"al3-interpretive\">\u003Cspan class=\"linenumber\">3\u003C/span>[\u003Cspan dir=\"ltr\" class=\"gap\">---\u003C/span>]USUIS\u003Cspan dir=\"ltr\" class=\"gap\">.\u003C/span>[\u003Cspan dir=\"ltr\" class=\"gap\">---\u003C/span>] \u003C/span>\u003C/div>  \u003Cp class=\"miniapp\">\u003C/p>",{"html":255},{"id":261,"lang":137,"html":262},"edition-diplomatic","\u003Cdiv class=\"textpart\" lang=\"la\">\u003Cspan class=\"ab\" id=\"div-diplomatic\">\u003Ca id=\"al1-diplomatic\">\u003C!--0-->\u003C/a>\u003Cspan class=\"linenumber\">1\u003C/span>[\u003Cspan dir=\"ltr\" class=\"gap\">---\u003C/span>]....\u003Cspan dir=\"ltr\" class=\"gap\">···\u003C/span>[\u003Cspan dir=\"ltr\" class=\"gap\">---\u003C/span>]\u003Cbr id=\"al2-diplomatic\">\u003Cspan class=\"linenumber\">2\u003C/span>[\u003Cspan dir=\"ltr\" class=\"gap\">---\u003C/span>.....].OREMFACI[..\u003Cspan dir=\"ltr\" class=\"gap\">---\u003C/span>]\u003Cbr id=\"al3-diplomatic\">\u003Cspan class=\"linenumber\">3\u003C/span>[\u003Cspan dir=\"ltr\" class=\"gap\">---\u003C/span>]USUIS\u003Cspan dir=\"ltr\" class=\"gap\">·\u003C/span>[\u003Cspan dir=\"ltr\" class=\"gap\">---\u003C/span>]\u003C/span>\u003C/div>\u003Cp class=\"miniapp\">\u003C/p>",[264,266,269,271],{"image":110,"thumb":265,"title":113},"ISic004360_tiled-thumb.tif",{"image":267,"thumb":268,"title":113},"ISic004360.jpg","ISic004360-thumb.jpg",{"image":116,"thumb":270,"title":113},"ISic004360_rear_tiled-thumb.tif",{"image":272,"thumb":273,"title":113},"ISic004360_rear.jpg","ISic004360_rear-thumb.jpg",[275],{"html":276},"Relatively tall and thin letters, but still of regular square form, of somewhat irregular width, with short basic serifs at the end of strokes; somewhat roughly chiselled. R has an extended tail which does not reach to the lower line; O is tall and narrow; E has slightly shorter middle stroke. M is narrow, with very short middle strokes that join at the midpoint and join the verticals well below the top.","\u003C?xml version='1.0' encoding='UTF-8'?>\n\u003C?xml-model href=\"https://epidoc.stoa.org/schema/latest/tei-epidoc.rng\" type=\"application/xml\" schematypens=\"http://relaxng.org/ns/structure/1.0\"?>\n\u003C?xml-model href=\"../schematron/ircyr-checking.sch\" schematypens=\"http://purl.oclc.org/dsdl/schematron\"?>\n\u003CTEI xmlns=\"http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0\" xmlns:xi=\"http://www.w3.org/2001/XInclude\" xml:lang=\"en\">\n    \u003CteiHeader>\n        \u003CfileDesc>\n            \u003CtitleStmt>\n                \u003Ctitle>I.Sicily inscription 004360\u003C/title>\n                \u003Ceditor ref=\"#JP\">Jonathan Prag\u003C/editor>\n                \u003Cprincipal ref=\"#JP\">Jonathan Prag\u003C/principal>\n                \u003Cfunder>John Fell OUP Research Fund\u003C/funder>\n\t   \u003Cfunder>\u003Cref target=\"https://cordis.europa.eu/project/id/885040\">ERC Advanced Grant no.885040\u003C/ref>\u003C/funder>\n                \u003CrespStmt>\n                    \u003Cname xml:id=\"JP\" ref=\"http://orcid.org/0000-0003-3819-8537\">Jonathan Prag\u003C/name>\n                    \u003Cresp>original data collection and editing\u003C/resp>\n                \u003C/respStmt>\n                \u003CrespStmt>\n                    \u003Cname xml:id=\"JCu\" ref=\"http://orcid.org/0000-0002-6686-3728\">James Cummings\u003C/name>\n                    \u003Cresp>conversion to EpiDoc\u003C/resp>\n                \u003C/respStmt>\n\t    \u003CrespStmt>\n     \t       \u003Cname xml:id=\"SS\" ref=\"https://orcid.org/0000-0003-3914-9569\">Simona Stoyanova\u003C/name>\n     \t       \u003Cresp>standardisation of template and tidying up encoding\u003C/resp>\n \t   \u003C/respStmt>\n                \u003CrespStmt>\n                    \u003Cname xml:id=\"VM\" ref=\"https://orcid.org/0000-0002-7122-2511\">Valentina Mignosa\u003C/name>\n                    \u003Cresp>encoding text division and checking the edition\u003C/resp>\n                \u003C/respStmt>\n            \u003CrespStmt>\u003Cname xml:id=\"Coccato\" ref=\"https://orcid.org/0000-0002-6641-2820\">Alessia Coccato\u003C/name>\u003Cresp>Petrographic observation and analysis\u003C/resp>\u003C/respStmt>\n            \u003C/titleStmt>\n            \u003CpublicationStmt>\n                \u003Cauthority>I.Sicily\u003C/authority>\n                \u003Cidno type=\"filename\">ISic004360\u003C/idno>\n                \u003Cidno type=\"TM\"/>\n                \u003Cidno type=\"EDR\"/>\n                \u003Cidno type=\"EDH\"/>\n                \u003Cidno type=\"EDCS\"/>\n                \u003Cidno type=\"PHI\"/>\n                \u003Cidno type=\"URI\">http://sicily.classics.ox.ac.uk/inscription/ISic004360\u003C/idno>\n                \u003Cidno type=\"DOI\" when=\"2020-12-23\">10.5281/zenodo.4390386\u003C/idno>\n                \u003Cavailability>\n                    \u003Clicence target=\"http://creativecommons.org/licenses/by/4.0/\">Licensed under a Creative Commons-Attribution 4.0 licence\u003C/licence>\n                \u003C/availability>\n            \u003C/publicationStmt>\n            \u003CsourceDesc>\n                \u003CmsDesc>\n                    \u003CmsIdentifier>\n                        \u003Ccountry>Italy\u003C/country>\n                        \u003Cregion>Sicily\u003C/region>\n                        \u003Csettlement>Siracusa\u003C/settlement>\n                        \u003Crepository role=\"museum\" ref=\"http://sicily.classics.ox.ac.uk/museum/097\">Museo Archeologico Regionale Paolo Orsi\u003C/repository>\n                        \u003Cidno type=\"inventory\">255\u003C/idno>\n                        \u003C!--Adding location for old id numbers if available-->\n                        \u003CaltIdentifier>\n                            \u003Csettlement/>\n                            \u003Crepository/>\n                            \u003Cidno type=\"old\"/>\n                        \u003C/altIdentifier>\n                    \u003C/msIdentifier>\n                    \u003CmsContents>\n                        \u003CtextLang mainLang=\"la\">Latin\u003C/textLang>\n                    \u003C/msContents>\n                    \u003CphysDesc>\n                        \u003CobjectDesc>\n                            \u003CsupportDesc>\n                                \u003Csupport>\u003Cp>Fragment of a marble plaque, broken on all sides (and with a break upper left but reattached); thickest upper left, slightly thinner at the base.\u003C/p>\n                                    \u003Cmaterial ana=\"#material.inorganic.stone.metamorphic_rock.marble\" type=\"stone.marble\" subtype=\"unspecified\" resp=\"#Coccato\" ref=\"http://www.eagle-network.eu/voc/material/lod/48.html\">marble\u003C/material>\n                                    \u003CobjectType ana=\"#object.plaque\" ref=\"http://www.eagle-network.eu/voc/objtyp/lod/259\">plaque\u003C/objectType>\n                                    \u003Cdimensions>\n                                        \u003Cheight unit=\"cm\">20.3\u003C/height>\n                                        \u003Cwidth unit=\"cm\">30\u003C/width>\n                                        \u003Cdepth unit=\"cm\">5.1-5.6\u003C/depth>\n                                    \u003C/dimensions>\n                                \u003C/support>\n                                \u003Ccondition ana=\"#condition.fragment\"/>\n\t\t    \u003C/supportDesc>\n                            \u003ClayoutDesc>\n                                \u003Clayout>\u003Cp>Remains of three lines of text, of which only the middle line is preserved to full height. Text is laid out between double guidelines.\u003C/p>\n                                    \u003Crs ana=\"#execution.chiselled\" ref=\"http://www.eagle-network.eu/voc/writing/lod/1\">chiselled\u003C/rs>\n                                \t\u003Cdamage ana=\"#text_condition.incomplete #text_condition.legible\"/>\n\t\t\t\u003C/layout>\n                            \u003C/layoutDesc>\n                        \u003C/objectDesc>\n                        \u003ChandDesc>\n                            \u003ChandNote>\u003Cp>Relatively tall and thin letters, but still of regular square form, of somewhat irregular width, with short basic serifs at the end of strokes; somewhat roughly chiselled. R has an extended tail which does not reach to the lower line; O is tall and narrow; E has slightly shorter middle stroke. M is narrow, with very short middle strokes that join at the midpoint and join  the verticals well below the top.\u003C/p>\n                                \u003Clocus from=\"line2\" to=\"line2\">Line 2\u003C/locus>\n                                \u003Cdimensions type=\"letterHeight\">\n                                    \u003Cheight unit=\"mm\" atLeast=\"70\" atMost=\"75\">70-75\u003C/height>\n                                \u003C/dimensions>\n                                \u003Clocus from=\"line1\" to=\"line2\">Interlineation line 1 to 2\u003C/locus>\n                                \u003Cdimensions type=\"interlinear\">\n                                    \u003Cheight unit=\"mm\" atLeast=\"17\" atMost=\"23\">17-23\u003C/height>\n                                \u003C/dimensions>\n                                \u003Clocus from=\"line2\" to=\"line3\">Interlineation line 2 to 3\u003C/locus>\n                                \u003Cdimensions type=\"interlinear\">\n                                    \u003Cheight unit=\"mm\" atLeast=\"25\" atMost=\"30\">25-30\u003C/height>\n                                \u003C/dimensions>\n                            \u003C/handNote>\n                        \u003C/handDesc>\n                    \u003C/physDesc>\n                    \u003Chistory>\n                        \u003Corigin>\n                            \u003CorigPlace>\u003Cregion>Sicilia\u003C/region>\n                                \u003CplaceName type=\"ancient\" ref=\"http://pleiades.stoa.org/places/462503\">Syracusae\u003C/placeName>\t\t\n                                \u003CplaceName type=\"modern\" ref=\"http://sws.geonames.org/2523083\">Siracusa\u003C/placeName>\n                            \t\u003Cgeo>37.08415, 15.27628\u003C/geo>\n\t\t\u003C/origPlace>\n                            \u003CorigDate datingMethod=\"#julian\" notBefore-custom=\"0151\" notAfter-custom=\"0400\" evidence=\"lettering material-context\">later imperial (later 2nd — 4th centuries CE?)\u003C/origDate>\n                        \u003C/origin>\n                        \u003Cprovenance type=\"found\" notAfter=\"1885\">Of uncertain provenance, first noted in the first volume of the museum inventory, compiled in 1885\u003C/provenance>\n                        \u003Cprovenance type=\"observed\">Magazzino B, cassetta 16\u003C/provenance>\n                        \u003Cprovenance type=\"observed\" subtype=\"autopsied\" when=\"2015-01-16\" resp=\"#JP\">Prag, 16.05.2015\u003C/provenance>\n                        \u003Cacquisition/>\n                    \u003C/history>\n                    \n                \u003C/msDesc>\n            \u003C/sourceDesc>\n        \u003C/fileDesc>\n        \u003CencodingDesc>\n             \u003Cp>Encoded following the latest EpiDoc guidelines\u003C/p>\n             \u003Cxi:include href=\"../alists/ISicily-taxonomies.xml\">\n                 \u003Cxi:fallback>\n                     \u003Cp>Taxonomies for ISicily controlled values\u003C/p>\n                 \u003C/xi:fallback>\n             \u003C/xi:include>\n\t  \u003Cxi:include href=\"../alists/charDecl.xml\">\n\t     \u003Cxi:fallback>\n\t       \u003Cp>ISicily glyphs authority list\u003C/p>\n\t     \u003C/xi:fallback>\n\t   \u003C/xi:include>\n         \u003C/encodingDesc>\n        \u003CprofileDesc>\n            \u003CcalendarDesc>\n                \u003Ccalendar xml:id=\"julian\">\n                    \u003Cp>Julian Calendar\u003C/p>\n                \u003C/calendar>\n            \u003C/calendarDesc>\n            \u003ClangUsage>\n                \u003Clanguage ident=\"en\">English\u003C/language>\n                \u003Clanguage ident=\"it\">Italian\u003C/language>\n                \u003Clanguage ident=\"grc\">Ancient Greek\u003C/language>\n                \u003Clanguage ident=\"la\">Latin\u003C/language>\n                \u003Clanguage ident=\"he\">Hebrew\u003C/language>\n                \u003Clanguage ident=\"phn\">Phoenician\u003C/language>\n                \u003Clanguage ident=\"xpu\">Punic\u003C/language>\n                \u003Clanguage ident=\"osc\">Oscan\u003C/language>\n                \u003Clanguage ident=\"xly\">Elymian\u003C/language>\n                \u003Clanguage ident=\"scx\">Sikel\u003C/language>\n                \u003Clanguage ident=\"sxc\">Sikan\u003C/language>\n            \u003C/langUsage>\n            \u003CtextClass>\n                \u003Ckeywords scheme=\"https://ontology.inscriptiones.org/type_of_inscription\">\n                    \u003Cterm ana=\"#function.building\" ref=\"https://ontology.inscriptiones.org/type_of_inscription/Building_inscription\">building\u003C/term>\n                \u003C/keywords>\n            \u003C/textClass>\n        \u003C/profileDesc>\n        \u003CrevisionDesc status=\"edited\">\n            \u003ClistChange>\n                   \u003Cchange when=\"2016-12-03\" who=\"#JCu\">James Cummings autogenerated EpiDoc output from database\u003C/change>\n            \t   \u003Cchange when=\"2020-10-05\" who=\"#SS\">Simona Stoyanova normalised Unicode\u003C/change>\n            \t   \u003Cchange when=\"2020-10-08\" who=\"#SS\">Simona Stoyanova updated list of languages\u003C/change>\n            \t   \u003Cchange when=\"2020-11-26\" who=\"#SS\">Simona Stoyanova restructured bibliography\u003C/change>\n\t   \u003Cchange when=\"2020-12-23\" who=\"#JP\">Updated Zenodo DOI\u003C/change>\n            \t   \u003Cchange when=\"2021-01-19\" who=\"#SS\">renumbered files, uris and references\u003C/change>\n                   \u003Cchange when=\"2021-01-25\" who=\"#VM\">Valentina Mignosa encoded text division, cleaned up the autogenerated text and checked the edition\u003C/change>\n                \u003Cchange when=\"2021-03-03\" who=\"#JP\">Jonathan Prag edited from autopsy, revising text, adding image, bibliography, metadata\u003C/change>\n            \u003C/listChange>\n        \u003C/revisionDesc>\n    \u003C/teiHeader>\n    \u003Cfacsimile>\n        \u003Csurface type=\"front\">\n            \u003Cgraphic n=\"screen\" url=\"ISic004360_tiled.tif\" height=\"3680px\" width=\"5520px\">\n                \u003Cdesc>Photo J. Prag, Aut. Assessorato Beni Culturali Regione Siciliana n.10681 del 06/05/2014\u003C/desc>\n            \u003C/graphic>\n            \u003Cgraphic n=\"print\" url=\"ISic004360.jpg\" height=\"3680px\" width=\"5520px\">\n                \u003Cdesc>Photo J. Prag, Aut. Assessorato Beni Culturali Regione Siciliana n.10681 del 06/05/2014\u003C/desc>\n            \u003C/graphic>\n        \u003C/surface>\n        \u003Csurface type=\"rear\">\n            \u003Cgraphic n=\"screen\" url=\"ISic004360_rear_tiled.tif\" height=\"3680px\" width=\"5520px\">\n                \u003Cdesc>Photo J. Prag, Aut. Assessorato Beni Culturali Regione Siciliana n.10681 del 06/05/2014\u003C/desc>\n            \u003C/graphic>\n            \u003Cgraphic n=\"print\" url=\"ISic004360_rear.jpg\" height=\"3680px\" width=\"5520px\">\n                \u003Cdesc>Photo J. Prag, Aut. Assessorato Beni Culturali Regione Siciliana n.10681 del 06/05/2014\u003C/desc>\n            \u003C/graphic>\n        \u003C/surface>\n    \u003C/facsimile>\n    \u003Ctext>\n        \u003Cbody>\n            \u003Cdiv type=\"edition\" subtype=\"primary\" xml:space=\"preserve\" xml:lang=\"la\" resp=\"#JP\">\n                \u003Cab>\n                    \u003Clb n=\"1\"/>\u003Cgap reason=\"lost\" extent=\"unknown\" unit=\"character\"/>\u003Corig>\u003Cunclear>RIAM\u003C/unclear>\u003C/orig>\u003Cgap reason=\"illegible\" unit=\"character\" quantity=\"3\"/>\u003Cgap reason=\"lost\" extent=\"unknown\" unit=\"character\"/>\n                    \u003Clb n=\"2\"/>\u003Cgap reason=\"lost\" extent=\"unknown\" unit=\"character\"/> \u003Csupplied reason=\"lost\">in\u003C/supplied> \u003Csupplied reason=\"lost\">mel\u003C/supplied>\u003Cunclear>i\u003C/unclear>orem faci\u003Csupplied reason=\"lost\">em\u003C/supplied>\u003Cgap reason=\"lost\" extent=\"unknown\" unit=\"character\"/>\n                    \u003Clb n=\"3\"/>\u003Cgap reason=\"lost\" extent=\"unknown\" unit=\"character\"/>\u003Corig>USUIS\u003C/orig>\u003Cgap reason=\"illegible\" unit=\"character\" quantity=\"1\"/>\u003Cgap reason=\"lost\" extent=\"unknown\" unit=\"character\"/>\n                \u003C/ab>\n            \u003C/div>\n            \u003Cdiv type=\"apparatus\" resp=\"#JP\">\n                \u003ClistApp>\n                    \u003Capp loc=\"line 1\">\u003Cnote>Orsi (NSA): Riam. . . .; Orsi (Taccuini): RIAMIR .  The first three characters are almost certainly RIA, followed by four verticals grouped in two pairs, either or both of which would be compatible with M as in line 2, followed by two further marks slightly above the line; Orsi's suggestion is entirely plausible.\u003C/note>\u003C/app>\n                    \u003Capp loc=\"line 2\">\u003Cnote>Orsi: IOREMFACI; the top of a vertical is visible at the start of the line\u003C/note>\u003C/app>\n                    \u003Capp loc=\"line 3\">\u003Cnote>The trace of a downward right slanting stroke is visible at the upper right end of the line, compatible with V, X or Y (also noted by Orsi, Taccuini)\u003C/note>\u003C/app>\n                    \u003C/listApp>\n            \u003C/div>\n            \u003Cdiv type=\"translation\">\n                \u003Cp>\u003C!--translation(s) - add @xml:lang for 'en' or 'it' to div-->\u003C/p>\n            \u003C/div>\n            \u003Cdiv type=\"commentary\" resp=\"#JP\">\n                \u003Cp>This text is on the reverse of what was originally a large monumental Latin inscription of the first or second century AD (see \u003Cref target=\"http://sicily.classics.ox.ac.uk/inscription/ISic001671\">ISic001671\u003C/ref>), and so this text is presumably secondary re-use of the stone and the later text from its form. Line 2 can reasonably be restored to suggest that this was a text recording the rebuilding or reconstruction of a structure of some sort. On that basis, the word in line 1 is perhaps most likely to be 'memoria' or 'gloria', and line 3 may contain reference to the individual responsible. The text does not appear to have been republished or discussed since Orsi. Orsi recorded it in the first of his taccuini, prior to publishing it in the NSA. Curiously, in neither case did he note the presence of a text on the reverse, which fact is recorded in the inventory (it is possible that the text was already fixed to the wall for display when he saw it?).\u003C/p>\n            \u003C/div>\n            \u003Cdiv type=\"bibliography\">\n                \u003ClistBibl type=\"edition\">\n                    \u003Cbibl type=\"bulletin\" n=\"NSA\">\n                        \u003Cauthor>Orsi\u003C/author>\n                        \u003Ctitle>NSA\u003C/title>\n                        \u003Cdate>1889\u003C/date>\n                        \u003CcitedRange>386\u003C/citedRange>\n                        \u003Cptr target=\"https://www.zotero.org/groups/382445/items/4MCP2PVV\"/>\n                    \u003Cref target=\"https://biblio.inscriptiones.org/epig10001392\">https://biblio.inscriptiones.org/epig10001392\u003C/ref>\u003C/bibl>\n                    \u003Cbibl>\n                        \u003Cauthor>Orsi\u003C/author>\n                        \u003Cdate>2018\u003C/date>\n                        \u003CcitedRange>Tacc. 1, p.46\u003C/citedRange>\n                        \u003Cptr target=\"https://www.zotero.org/groups/382445/items/RGRSRUHK\"/>\n                    \u003Cref target=\"https://biblio.inscriptiones.org/epig10002617\">https://biblio.inscriptiones.org/epig10002617\u003C/ref>\u003C/bibl>\n                \u003C/listBibl>\n\t   \u003ClistBibl type=\"discussion\">\u003Cbibl/>\u003C/listBibl>\n            \u003C/div>\n        \u003C/body>\n    \u003C/text>\n\u003C/TEI>\n"],"uses":{"params":["slug"]}}]}
